HEADWORD: Earthenware
<hw>Earth"en*ware`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Vessels and
other utensils, ornaments, or the like, made of baked clay. See
<er>Crockery</er>, <er>Pottery</er>, <er>Stoneware</er>, and
<er>Porcelain</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

